{"type":"message","id":"4d3b4919","parentId":"dfe333a9","timestamp":"2026-03-25T02:52:05.981Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the HEARTBEAT.md and run through the scheduled tasks.\n\nHEARTBEAT.md says:\n- Core Rules:\n  - Reply HEARTBEAT_OK if nothing new\n  - Quiet hours 23:00-08:00\n  - Only 3 types of proactive alerts: new files/reports, script results, user input needed\n\n- Scheduled Work:\n  1. Workspace backup - daily\n  2. Quant ops - pre-market 09:20-09:40 + daily audit\n  3. Self-improvement - daily afternoon/evening\n\n- Active Task Monitoring:\n  - Check ACTIVE_TASK.md\n  - If Status=active and Next has content, spawn subagent or sessions_yield\n\nCurrent time: 10:51 AM - well past quiet hours.\n- Quant ops: The three subagent tasks (quant-mainline-health, quant-enhancements, quant-daily-audit) already ran at 09:15 AM (they completed successfully from earlier heartbeats).\n- Workspace backup: No subagent spawned for this yet.\n\n\n- Self-improvement: Could be triggered\n\nSince the quant ops tasks already completed at 09:15 AM with OK/PASS results and no blocking issues, and it's now mid-morning, I should check if there are any active tasks or pending items that need attention before deciding whether to trigger the backup or other scheduled work.\n\nLooking at the three completed tasks - mainline-health, enhancements, and daily-audit - they all passed, but daily-audit flagged some items to watch: real trading automation readiness is still false, the recent automated pre-market check is blocked, old automatic rules persist in HEARTBEAT, and the strict precheck gate remains in place. The ACTIVE_TASK.md is marked done with nothing in progress, so these are just observations to monitor going forward.\n\nChecking the scheduled work, workspace-backup has a checklist reference but no indication it ran today, and self-improvement hasn't been triggered yet. Given that the core systems are healthy and there's n