{"type":"message","id":"5d340756","parentId":"91cd5775","timestamp":"2026-03-25T04:41:25.407Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The exit code 1 means grep found no matches (since all the deleted files match `.deleted.` or `.reset.`). Let me think about what modified files are NOT session/cron artifacts:\n\nModified files that are NOT session/cron artifacts:\n- `M agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json` - SENSITIVE\n- `M agents/main/agent/models.json` - safe to commit\n- `M agents/main/sessions/sessions.json` - safe (operational file)\n- `M cron/jobs.json` - safe to commit\n- `M identity/device-auth.json` - SENSITIVE\n- `M memory/codex-bridge/bridge_state.json` - safe\n\n\n- `M memory/coding-agent.sqlite` - safe\n- `M memory/memos-primary/mirror_state.json` - safe\n- `M openclaw.json` - safe to commit\n- `M skills/weibo-monitor/logs/weibo_monitor.err` - safe (log)\n- `M skills/weibo-monitor/scripts/fetch_weibo.py` - safe\n- `M skills/weibo-monitor/scripts/fetch_weibo_v2.py` - safe\n- `M subagents/runs.json` - safe\n- `M workspace` - could be anything\n\nNow I'm looking at the untracked directories that should be excluded from commits: `.clawhub/`, `.firecrawl/`, `.openclaw/`, `.vscode/`, and `Modelfile` all need to be ignored since they're cache or generated content. There are also several agent-related directories like `agents/backup/`, `agents/coder-lite/`, `agents/codex/`, `agents/coding-agent/`, and `agents/downloader/` that appear to be untracked as well.\n\nFor the actual backup strategy, I think the right move is to update `.gitignore` to exclude all session artifacts and deleted session files, then stage only the genuinely safe modified files for commit—things like `agents/main/agent/models.json`, `cron/jobs.json`, and `openclaw.json`. I'll leave the sensitive files and the giant pile of untracked session garbage for now since this is getting complicated. I'm reconsidering the approach here—the heartbeat has already waited